Many things many linguists should know about the creation, evaluation, and use of corpora* (* But sometimes don't bother to ask.)

Felix Bildhauer, Institut für Deutsche Sprache Mannheim
Roland Schäfer, Freie Universität Berlin (alphabetically)

CC-BY text book about corpus creation and use for linguists, based on DGfS-CL
2017 Fall School course: http://rolandschaefer.net/?p=1382


TECHNICAL NOTES

* The subdirectories figures/ and cache/ are for knitr-generated content only! Never check them in with git, never manually store anything in them!

* Directory for custom images is images/

* Never add knitr-generated TeX files to git!

* The Inconsolata-g font can be obtained here: http://www.fantascienza.net/leonardo/ar/inconsolatag/inconsolata-g_font.zip

* Inconsolata-g installation on Ubuntu:

> sudo mkdir /usr/share/fonts/truetype/customfonts
> sudo cp Inconsolatar.ttf /usr/share/fonts/truetype/customfonts/
> sudo fc-cache -fv
